ated Catholic take on current political and social realities—realities that are not confined to France alone—A Brief Apology for a Catholic Moment is a valuable contribution to a larger conversation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aChurch and statezFrance. 0aLaicismzFrance. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  alaïcité, laicity, the common good, decadence, nihilism, trinitarian experience of God.1 aHart, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewis, Stephen E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021 Englishz978311075415508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021z9783110753929oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226691398423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226691398/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075415-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DPHb2021